column51: In between 75 and 150 words, please describe your personality in free text.

I am a very open-minded, polite person and always crave new experiences. At work I manage a team of software developers and we often have to come up with new ideas.  I went to college and majored in computer science, and enjoyed the experience.  I have met many like-minded people and I enjoy speaking with them about a lot of various topics. I am sometimes shy around people who I don't know well, but I try to be welcoming and warm to everyone I meet. I try to do something fun every week, even if I'm quite busy, like having a BBQ or watching a movie. I have a wife whom I love and we live together in a nice single-family home.

I dislike the idea of having to talk to people I don't know and making small talk. I think its a waste of time if I am not going to see them again, and I do not trust people I do not know enough to actually invest my time in them, as for people I do know I give them my undivided attention. If I have to be a party or group function, I will stick to the people I know, or just hang back and enjoy myself without talking to others, only talking to those that I need to. I feel it allows me to not stress so much considering I tend to take on other peoples problems.

I enjoy meeting people and talking to them, learning about them and their lives. I like to help others, and think I'm a caring person. I am a hard worker and take pride in making sure that I do my best at all times. I have a good imagination and really enjoy reading and listening to music. I don't always follow a routine because I enjoy taking each day as it comes. I think that I am a kind hearted person in general, and avoid disruption in my life.

I am often uncomfortable and self-conscious around people I don't know well. I have a lot of anxiety in social situations and avoid them if it's possible. When I do become close to someone though I am happy to spend time with them and share in experiences. Mentally I try and put myself in other people's shoes and give them the benefit of the doubt, but emotionally I tend to be critical and uncaring about other people's problems despite feeling guilty for feeling that way. I constantly fret about things and it always seems like my mind is going in a hundred different directions at once so I become irritated extremely easily out of frustration and stress.

I personally like to take time to help people as much as I possibly can. I usually try to make sure people are comfortable at first and then I talk to them deeply about issue, and then try to solve those issues as best as I can. I try to make my presence known and keep people interested in a way that keeps people calm, but entertained. I also try to make other people's success my own success. I try to help push people to the next level, and if they reach that with my help, I feel I succeeded as that was my personal task.

My personality has many facets. For the most part, I am pretty outgoing. I am able to talk to just about anyone pretty easily. As well, I am a very good listener. I'm willing to hear people out and do my best to relate to and empathize with their situation. 
I'm uncomfortable being the center of attention and am more comfortable interacting in small groups.
I am exceedingly patient and very, very rarely lose my cool or get angry. I value close relationships, deep conversation, and laughter. I have a really good sense of humor. This allows me to put others at ease. All in all, I am a pretty easy going person.

In term of my personalities, I tend to keep my emotions to myself and opt to avoid social situations. I don't like to mingle with others and otherwise will avoid activities that relies on interacting with others. While I can accept others for who they are and have high tolerance for others, I tend to avoid getting close in relationship situations. I am also someone who can be diligent in their work but can also give up if I feel that I'm not up to the task. I'm also somewhat of a fearful person who avoid risks and take things at a slow pace.

I am mainly a person that worries a lot. I tend to be nervous as I worry about bad things that might happen. I also feel the need to be prepared and organized. I am moody as I do like to experience happiness, but worry drags my mood down and then I become worrisome, blue, and irritable. I would like to be carefree but that is extremely difficult for me. I tend not to be extroverted around people because I have an intense fear of being judged. I don't like myself much and I automatically assume people are going to see the worst in me and so I really try to keep to myself to avoid being hurt or embarrassed. On my own I do feel happy around my son, and when I am working alone or participating in hobbies that I enjoy. Because I am alone a lot I feel uncomfortable being around people and I feel awkward trying to interact with others or start conversations in social settings. I will respond if people talk to me but it's hard for me to think of things to talk about that won't put me in a position of being judged.

I think of myself as someone who tries to do the right thing and who tries to follow the rules. I have ideally just wanted to do my own thing and be in control of things for myself. I have a tendency to overreact or overthink situations and I can get stuck in thought loops pretty easily. I want to be able to do what is best for me but I try not to hurt anyone. My mind is very busy.

The personality of mine is happy person , easily join hands with others to have fun in any moment. Also have a good understanding of people around me and many people founds me amazing and the time passes for people who spends time with me. Friends of mine have more knowledge of outer surroundings and the news about the whole world. I like to speak , discuss and argue with those people mostly because I like to gather more knowledge. Totally i have the thrust for knowledge and fun.

i am friendly person. i always likes to be in touch of people. i love to share my things with others. i expect too much. i gets disappoint easily. i am soft hearted. i am hardworking and do anything to get what i want. i help others beyond my limits. i feel others pain. I never forgets anyone favour. if someone loves me i loves two time. \i feel disappoint and disturbed when someone cheats on me. I am fun loving and very friendly to everyone around me.

I feel I am a quite even-keeled person when it comes to introversion versus extroversion.  I do not mind being the life of the party when it comes time to cut loose and get wild, but deep down I have a strong preference for lounging around by my lonesome and mellowing out with some games and music.  I like talking to people but at the same time I often prefer the company of my cats over the company of other human beings.  An ex girlfriend of mine used to call me a chameleon!

I have always considered myself to be a good listener and a watcher of life. This trait of mine has been the fundamental source of my strength. It's the rainfall of my inner tears that has watered the seeds of the poetic and the philosophical side of me. I thrive on emotion and reason. I know that sounds like a conundrum but I was born a Gemini so what can I tell you. Even when I was a little boy under five years old, any significant emotion (especially sadness, anger, and jealousy) was always so hard for me. No one taught me how to identify or manage my feelings so I was on my own.

I am creative and have a lot of interest in art, music, writing and learning things. I seek knowledge and like to reflect on abstract ideas. I admire people who put in the effort to have original ideas and thoughts. I dislike dishonesty and lack of integrity. I have no respect for corrupt and greedy people who prey on other people to get ahead. I believe in working hard and working smart for the goals and dreams you have. I also like to have peace of mind and not engage in gossip or conflicts. I tend to avoid people that are confrontational and manipulative. I like to help people that are deserving and are trying to better themselves.

I am very much honest and straight forward. I want freedom in my life to go any where and do anything as i wish. I dont like control on me. I like to keep people happy around me. I like travelling to different places ad meet different people. I easily make friendship to all. I like veg food more than non veg. Masala items i like most. Ice cream is my favourite food ever. I believe in god. I like to visit more ancient  temples and like to know its history.

My attitude is very smart when i am working in my office i am very talented person compare then other staff frequently my manager told to my other staff  and i love to cooking for my family members and purchasing a lot of thing for my family members and loved one i am really complex compare then other

I like to help other who really deserve it and is compassionate and caring and always want to be truthful and sincere and like to be clean and like to follow good proverbs and try to apply them in my life.

I’m very easy going. It doesn’t take a lot to make me happy. I don’t take anything for granted. Life is short and I was raised to always cherish family and friends to the fullest. I like living a simple life where I work hard and enjoy my off time.

i am usually a free minded person. I am usually motivated when going to office and doesn't neglect my duties and always try to be motivated and also try to motivate my colleagues. I like to help others who need genuine help. I am a simple guy and have a lovable and caring family. I usually don't take high risk. I am a low risk taker and always try to play safe. I work hard and want to work more harder to give happiness to my family.

My name is Archana Mishra but I am usually called by pet name Gudiya. I am 12 years old, studying in 7th standard.

I am the second child of my parents and have an elder brother. I live in a joint family with my uncle, grandparents and cousins ​​in the same large house.

We love each other very much and are connected to grandparents. I have a group of friends but Sanika is my best and true friend.

I can share anything with him and that too we study in the same school but in different classes. I love telling jokes to my friends in the bus after school time.

I have a unique family. All my family members are broad and open minded. They always encourage me to do well in every field.

They never pull me back and always inspire me. I am very happy to be born in this family.

My family is a cross-cultural extended family where my uncles, aunts, grandparents, cousins, etc. live together.

I have a great time with my family as we celebrate each festival together. I help the other children of the family to do household chores every day.

The second meaning emphasizes those qualities that make all people alike and that distinguish

i am a retired tutor. i love my family, friends, and Jesus. i am diligent, kind, and have a sense of humor. i like people and am very social but dont have a need to be around them all the time. i am smart and amusing.

I am  very  punctual  and want to  do  all  my  work  the  right time. I like  to  eat  plain  and  healthy  food. I enjoy  dancing  reading books, playing  badminton  and  cooking  in  my  spare  time. I  never  leave  my  classes  and  also  attend  every  class.  I  go  to  school  daily  in  proper  uniform.  I  do  well  in  exams  whether  main  or  class  tests. I have  many  friend  but  palaver  is  my best  friend.  There  are  many  people  in  the world  who  have  different personalities . I  am  a  very  responsible  and  sympathetic  person.  I  always  help  others  and  try my  best  to  solve  their  problem .

I would describe my personality as very outgoing and social. I am easy to talk to and a good listener. I understood people and I make friends very easily. I'm rather carefree guy. I like what I like which is a lot, but that can change in a snap. I am outgoing with  a great sense of humor. I am willing to help anyone in need and when I'm in I'm all in. I am fairly easy going. I have good leadership qualities and am confident of myself. I'm able to keep a calm and level head whenever I am in situation of stress.

I am someone who tries their best to be there for people, but that only happens when my resources are stocked in some fashion. It's hard sometimes to have the energy to do a lot of things and my constant thoughts sap a lot of my energy. I want to help people, but I sometimes do so at the expense of my own well-being. I just want everyone to get along and to live well. I want to be a role model for others, but the energy of getting there is daunting.

I am both simple and complex. I am like everyone but uniquely me. Beauty captivates me and I see it everywhere. I love people and cherish my time alone. I am good at many things and great at none. I love my home and have a constant urge to travel.I am both very practical and very creative. I am friendly with many people but friends with few. Those I love, I love fiercely.

I think there are different levels of my personality. I"m a hard worker who likes to get things done, but I also have a strong sense of humor.  I generally believe in work before play however.  I value relationships and people.  I like to do things efficiently so there is time to enjoy life. I am very competitive.  I enjoy being active and don't like to sit for vary long.

I'm strong-minded I believe in right is right no matter what the consequences. I'm a protector of children I feel like they are a gift from your creator and that it's your duty to do whatever to protect them so that they can mature to adulthood. I'm loyal and I believe that you should man up to all the decision one make no matter good or bad.

I am also very much open to new experiences. I am down to earth person and love simplicity.
i am a free moving girl who dont get tensed so easily. i always respect elders for their words.i have zero attitude towards everyone

I would describe my personality as approachable, light-hearted, and positive. I am quite, focused, and determined. I am energized, focused and motivated to do my best. I always take the high road and treat my family, leaders, colleagues, and team with respect.

I'm an overall caring person who is really concerned with others and wants the best outcomes in all situations. I can put too much effort into making sure others are doing the right thing while ignoring myself. I don't really like to talk a lot and I very often tend to stay quietly in the background ignoring what's going on around me. I try to avoid others which makes me more nervous anytime I have to interact and makes it difficult for me to socialize properly and get along with others in friendship ways.

I love my family and I am in love with my wife of 38 years. I like to work and make money. I also like to play, I like to fish and hunt. I like beautiful woman even though I am in love with my wife I will look at another woman especially if she is beautiful. I own my own business as I am a builder, I have been in business for 18 years, I build houses, garages and decks, my company specializes in building decks.

I am a person who loves people, babies, animals etc. I am an empath. I feel what they feel. I tend to be shy and quiet but once I am comfortable I open up. I like my own company and hate crowds. I prefer a small group of friends hanging out over a party or concert. I am responsible and always on time. I would rather have a job I love than one that pays more. My family is the best part of me

I am a very cooperative and compassionate person by nature who is interested in helping others.  I am a laid back person who doesn't worry about very much and use my optimism to see the bright side of things.  I am also a very active person  who loves to be on the move.  I am a social and outgoing person who enjoys being around people and trying to make them feel comfortable.  I don't love being the center of attention, but I also won't avoid it.

I am a calm, but passionate person who is very family oriented.  I have a regimented life that helps me accomplish my goals.  I enjoy interacting with many different types of people and try to make myself useful.  I wouldn't consider myself extroverted, but I do like to mingle with lots of people.  I prefer my life to be structured because it makes me feel calm.  I do not typically stress very much and have a positive attitude about most things.  I consider my mood to be stable.

My personality is annoying. I usually do not have much to say. But, when I get comfortable with someone, I talk too much. It is hard for me to disengage at that point. Other times I am serious. I do not make others uncomfortable though. Nobody has to walk on eggshells around me. I am accommodating and put people at ease. I have a pleasant attitude and rarely get sad. It is also very hard to make me angry.

I am a thoughtful person who tries to make people like me.  I try to be open minded but can be a little judgy when people are snobby.  I try to be outgoing and friendly to everyone.  I love  animals, shopping and being creative.  I am stubborn which sometimes isnt the best way to be.  I do like helping others.

I'm extrememly self aware and am always following my own truth so that I don't step on anyone's toes. I don't spend a lot of time thinking about people I don't mesh with, but I am very dedicated to my family and the friends that are very close to me.

I am a middle class boy. I was born on 01/12/1976. I was a govt. I went to school. I have passed higher secondary from there. Then I passed computer science from Calcutta university. I am now a software developer for a WIPRO company. I have been working here for 24 long years with dedication and concentration.

When it comes to me it all starts with being relaxed. I am a very relaxed person who goes with the flow of things. I am also not afraid to speak my mind even if people arent going to agree with me. I am not a people pleaser in general. I love being in control of the situation, I hate to rely on others as that means I have to wait on them to make decisions that affect my life. I am fun loving and love to have a good time and a good laugh. I am a good friend that will have you back.

My personality is different. I can easily switch back and forth from being calm to being totally stressed out. I like people but I prefer animals. I get very anxious of the unknown. Like when I start something new or something that is out of my control. I worry a lot about what if this happens or what if that happens. 

I am very concerned for other's well being. I don't like to see people get mistreated. I don't like  to see animals get mistreated. I have a very soft heart. 

I prefer to talk to people via text then face to face. I am kind of a loner.
i have a soft heart and i feel other peoples problems and i can talk a lot of different types of peoples in different types of parties.

I have an adaptive personality. I took the Myers Briggs and I am very introverted but I would call it situational introversion. When I need to be extroverted such as working and networking with others, I will be extroverted. But I would need a couple of days to relax and be myself.

I am pretty sensitive person. I an gentle spirited and kind. I can close off if I feel a sense of rejection. I am quiet and like my alone time but also like being around people from time to time. I am very introspective and have to keep myself in check from always over thinking. I can be in my head a lot as I am also a day dreamer. Most of the time I am pretty even in my emotions. I am a happy person who likes to encourage others to seek the best for themselves. I am a champion for others and I am that way for myself as well.

I have a dominating personality and controlling. I easily insult people and often rude to others, especially those that I don't like much. I don't take much of an interest in other peoples problems and am not very sympathetic of their problems. I am opinionated and unforgiving towards others.  I can become irritated and impatient with others quickly.  I often strive to be the leader and tend to take over conversations. I make a lot of jokes to make people laugh to draw attention to myself. I can talk to anyone and do not consider myself to be shy or timid around others.

I am a very introverted person. I tend to keep to myself and I like activities that are solitary. However, sometimes I get bored of this and want to go out and be around people. I am a hard worker at my job but sometimes it is hard to get motivated for my own personal goals. I try to be nice to people but sometimes I feel I get walked on due to my easy-going nature. I put others before me and am trying to work on my own self-care.

I am a very quiet person. I do not have a lot of friends, but I like it that way. I have a caring nature and try and help others when I can. Some of my favorite moments have been when I have worked as a volunteer at church or at the local soup kitchen. I am a perfectionist and exacting in my work. That can become a problem because I get easily upset if everything is not just the way I want it. I tend to be cynical because I have had a very difficult life with a lot of obstacles. I tend to get depressed very easily.

A creative problem solver. Can come up with a wide range of ideas. Caring of others, always willing to help. A sense of humor even during the worse of times. Can find the silver lining to bad situation. Trust just about everyone. A hard worker with some attention to detail but not so much that it is obsessive. Finds the good in everything including people. Assuming everyone means well unless proven otherwise through previous actions. Stubborn, sarcastic, never gives up.
I try to keep in the background. I've very quite around people I don't know. I have little to say around people I know. I'm quite and do not like to draw attention to myself.

I am someone who is very open to talk and have a good time with people I know and trust but am quick to become shy and reserved around strangers. I like to be the center of attention among my friends but definitely never want to be the center of attention when it comes to strangers. I'll go out of my way to help anyone with anything (within reason) and actively try to do things to make my friends and families lives easier.

I am a kind and friendly person. I get along well with others. I like to cooperate with people. I am easy going and relaxed most of the time. I can be a bit shy and inhibited, and it takes me a while to feel comfortable around strangers and people that I meet for the first time. I try to be helpful, and think of others before myself. I am a modest and humble person. I don't like to show off or attract too much attention to myself. I really care about taking care of animals and the environment. I am fairly exacting in my work and I pay attention to details.

Basically, I am an extrovert person and likes to mingle with people. I always love to be center of attraction. I am interested in learning new things and always prefer to spend maximum time in the library. I am very fond of flowers and like to decorate my house with different kind of indoor plants. Cooking is my hobby and I am very much interested in preparing a variety of cuisine. I love my family and I am a spiritual person, who believes in god and prey everyday. I believe in hard work and I hate people who are lazy and postpone work. Finally, I am a very health conscious person and always keep my place neat and hygienic.

I am a very empathetic person. I am a Christian practicing faith daily. That comprises my overall thoughts and actions. I try to hear others, be present, and help when possible. I would consider myself to be open to critique and use that to learn and grow. I really like serving others.

I tend to be curious. I like to investigate things. If I find myself wondering about something, I'll look it up. I enjoy knowing trivial facts. I find them interesting. I get very interested in a subject for a while, then move on to another one. I enjoy cooking. I value honesty. I try to think skeptically about things. I enjoy music and think about it often when I'm not listening to it. I've become very conscious of my health. I like humor a great deal and enjoy being with other people.

I am intelligent and engaged. I tend to be blue and depressed. I enjoy spending time with people and wish that I had more close friends. I keep my home neat and tidy. People say that I am a good listener. I enjoy movies and books. I am recently widowed and miss my husband deeply. I am religious and attend worship services frequently. I am content to spend a lot of my time completing surveys. This is satisfying to me.

I'm more reserved than I used to be, but overall I am a friendly and unassuming person. I make friends easily in situations like work, or places where you are forced to interact, and I have no problem making small talk or keeping a conversation going with someone I've just met. I do find that I get annoyed easily, though, and as I get older I find myself just avoiding situations that would make me uncomfortable rather than going through them and becoming agitated. I think I'm a trustworthy person, people seem open to revealing secrets to me, but I do find myself unwilling to get truly close to others. I'm more concerned with my own safety in that regard, as though I'm not suspicious of everyone, I would just rather not take risks in that realm currently. So while I'm not a "shut-in", I just find myself having less social contact than previously in my life, when I was more outgoing and would seek social activities more. I also value a good sense of humor.

I'm an introvert, but I like to be around people, who are close to me. I have an active imagination, I'm kind, caring and I'm successful in my career. My emotions tend to stay on an even level and I rarely get too high or too low. I work hard and try to better myself. I like learning, reading, athletics, fitness, nature and outdoor recreation. I do not like to be the center of attention, unless it is one-on-one with another person or in small groups. I hate public speaking. I like to eat healthy and exercise regularly to stay in shape.

I am generally quiet and prefer not to be the center of attention; however, I am capable of talking to others when I choose.  I dislike conflict and have found that it is easier to avoid confrontational conversations by simply staying quiet these days.  I used to be more outgoing and outspoken but I withdrew during COVID and the social turmoil over the last few years.  I prefer to keep to myself, but I enjoy reading, learning, and improving myself.  I am almost always happy and rarely feel upset, but I am empathetic when around or listening to my close friends.  I feel like I have a lot of interesting ideas at work and at home, but I only share them with people I trust.

I find myself to be generally interested in what people share with me and engage them on it even if it seems mundane initially. I have a strong sense of what mood someone is before they even start talking to me. I don't worry much about how others view me other than to not annoy them. I am usually quite inventive with problem solving too. I try to come at everyone warmly no matter what. I have many artistic and technical interests, partly because I dislike being idle or feel I'm just waiting around.

I think in general I'm a fairly nervous person, who worries too much about things, even when they don't really matter. I feel like I'm always anxious about something, whether it's something small and unimportant, or something that actually has real consequences. This makes it quite difficult for me to relax. I also tend to be prone to feelings of low mood, sadness, or depression. I like talking to people but it often takes me a while before I feel comfortable with someone. I think I'm also pretty kind and try to be generous. I try to listen to my friends if they're having issues, and will offer help or advice if possible. I tend to be overly cautious in some situations, and try to not take unnecessary risks. I'm also not very assertive, and have a tendency to go along with what other people want to do.

I'm a trusting person, to a point.  To me, omitting pertinant information is lying.  Don't do that.  I am slow to warm up to others, especially face to face.  I'm highly suspicious of people I don't know.  I don't care much whether people like my outfits/ideas/etc. or not.  I'll listen to their input and give it consideration and have no issue with them for thinking differently from me.  I can get along with and be friends with people who aren't as liberal minded as I am.  I'm curious about science in most all aspects of it.  I will drop what I'm doing just because a person asked for my help with something.  It could be help in cleaning up or help finding something on the internet, or a small bit of typing.  I like to help others, provided I can.

I have a small but loyal group of friends that I prefer to be around.  I am intellectually curious.  I am relatively organized.  I like to plan out my day in advance.  I great frustrated and irritated if my plans are interfered with by other people.

I tend to be quite and reserved. I have a lot of thoughts on a variety of things, but I also feel that most of the time other people don't want to hear what I have to say. If you get me talking I will talk a lot, but I wont start a conversation. I prefer to have things orderly and in their place, and I can be a bit of a neat freak.

The biggest part of my personality is probably my sense of humor - I have been told that I am very funny. I can be persuasive, and sometimes a bit argumentative. Someone once told me that I take being nice very seriously which I guess is true. I don't like seeing people being mean to others for no reason and I try not to do so myself. I love learning new things. I can be lazy at times. I am often a little blue or anxious; I worry a lot, especially about the people I care about. I tend to be quite introverted, and often prefer to keep to myself. Sometimes I feel like I need a lot of personal space, even from loved ones.

I am someone who likes to question everything. I like to find the truth and then look at that even if its not something I want to see or if things aren't the way that I would choose. I am also not afraid to deal with things when they are difficult. I don't like to pretend or be dishonest. I like to deal with reality and if there is a problem I want to face it head on instead of pretending that it doesn't exist or ignoring it until it gets worse. I don't like to play games with others or use them for my personal gain. I like to listen to others and understand how they feel and where they are coming from. I like to see things from their point-of-view and empathize with them.

I am a trustworthy, honest, and humble person.I am very meticulous with my work.I work very hard.I love to be sociable and am described as a calm and relax person.Am taking responsibility for myself actions are admirable qualities.

I see myself as something of an introvert/extrovert by circumstance first of all. I would describe myself as being not exactly "shy" in the utmost stereotypical way, but also not verbose openly either/just talkative and friendly. I can talk with people, or groups, or one-on-one -- however, I would not consider myself extroverted even though I don't consider myself wholly shy either. I believe I am more of a sigma-esque type -- sociable when it's worthwhile/necessary, but "shy" when there's no reason to socialize AKA do not fit in or do not feel they'd dominate or be sufficient in said group or place.
